To the best of my knowledge, consuming a moderate amount of coffee can benefit our health in many ways. Firstly, research shows that drinking one or two cups of coffee a day may help reduce the risk of heart failure. Secondly, individuals who consume the amount of caffeine in two cups of coffee may receive significant protection against Alzheimer's disease and may be less likely to develop dementia. Thirdly, coffee drinkers are more likely to have liver enzyme levels within a healthy range compared to those who don't drink coffee.

It is widely believed that moderate coffee consumption offers several benefits. Studies suggest that drinking one or two cups per day may lower the risk of heart failure. Additionally, the caffeine equivalent of two cups of coffee has been linked into a reduced risk of Alzheimer's disease and dementia. Furthermore, regular coffee drinkers tend to maintain healthier liver enzyme levels compared to non-drinkers.
